<img src="https://i2.wp.com/www.bellanaija.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Air-Peace.png?ssl=1" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Well, actually, just in Lagos and Abuja. According to the Minister of Aviation, Hadi Sirika, Kano, Port Harcourt, Owerri and Maiduguri will resume on the 11th. This is coming only a few days after President Muhammadu Buhari relaxed the interstate travel ban. Other airports will resume on the 15th, and more better news: international flights will “be announced in due course.” I am glad to announce that Abuja & Lagos airports will resume domestic operations on the 8th of July, 2020. Kano, Port Harcourt, Owerri & Maiduguri to resume on the 11th. Other airports on the 15th. Date for international to be announced in due course. Bear with us, please — Hadi Sirika (@hadisirika) July 1, 2020 The post July 8 – That’s When Domestic Flights are Resuming appeared first on BellaNaija – Showcasing Africa to the world. Read today!. Original Article Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world.